schema:creator: Latour, Georges de
schema:description:
1 Southern Pacific shipping receipt for cuttings, consigned to Leopold Justi, February 17, 1904
2 Envelope addressed to Leopold Justi in Cordelia, dated April 12, 1905, containing example of fishing hooks and line, and at one time included a sample of bait
Billhead from Leopold Justi for bench grafts made out to a Mrs. [unreadable], March 4, 1908
3 Billhead from Leopold Justi for bench grafts made out to H.J. Chauvet, March 4, 1908
4 Southern Pacific Railroad freight bills made out to GDL, to be paid by M.C. Cleves. March 12, 1908 (3), March 4, 1909
5 Form letter introducing Leopold Justi as agent for GDL, c1907
6 California Northwestern Railway shipping receipt for vines, consigned to R.G. Hill, Eldridge [Robert P. Hill], February [ ], 1908
7 Southern Pacific shipping receipt, consigned to Leopold Justi, February 24, 1909
8 California Northwestern Railway shipping receipt for vines, for Leopold Justi, March 3 [undated]
9 Two pages of handwritten notes about grape varieties and pumps, probably by Leopold Justi
schema:name: Ephemera from Georges de Latour/Justi correspondence:, 1905-1908
